HEADWORD: Tephramancy
<hw>Teph"ra*man`cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ ashes
+ <ets>-mancy</ets>.]</ety> <def>Divination by the ashes of the altar on
which a victim had been consumed in sacrifice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

